  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Welcome to the first notebook of the **2026 ICAR GloFAS Training**. This notebook introduces the Copernicus Emergency Management Service (CEMS) **Early Warning Data Store (EWDS)** and shows you how to access **GloFAS Reanalysis** data – a long historical record of river discharge that is essential for flood risk analysis.\n",
    "\n",
    "We will use [**earthkit**](https://earthkit.readthedocs.io/en/stable/), ECMWF's modern Python toolkit, to access and explore the data with minimal code, before converting it to familiar formats such as `xarray` and `pandas` for analysis and visualisation."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## What this notebook does\n",
    "\n",
    "In this first tutorial, you will follow a complete beginner workflow for CEMS flood analysis: set up EWDS API access, retrieve GloFAS Reanalysis data using earthkit, inspect and convert the dataset, extract a river discharge time series, and produce key visualisations (hydrograph and monthly climatology)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Learning Objectives 🎯\n",
    "\n",
    "By the end of this notebook you will be able to:\n",
    "\n",
    "- Explain what the **CEMS Early Warning Data Store (EWDS)** is and how it relates to GloFAS\n",
    "- Set up programmatic access using your **EWDS API token**\n",
    "- Download **GloFAS Reanalysis** data using the `cdsapi` Python package\n",
    "- Access the same data more efficiently using **earthkit-data**\n",
    "- Inspect a dataset's structure and metadata with earthkit\n",
    "- Convert the data to an **xarray Dataset** for further analysis\n",
    "- Extract a **discharge time series** for a specific river location\n",
    "- Create an annotated **hydrograph** and a **monthly climatology** plot"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Background\n",
    "\n",
    "### What is GloFAS?\n",
    "\n",
    "The **Global Flood Awareness System (GloFAS)** is a global hydrological forecasting and early warning system developed by ECMWF in partnership with the European Commission. It provides:\n",
    "\n",
    "| Product | Description |\n",
    "|---|---|\n",
    "| **GloFAS Reanalysis** | Long historical record of river discharge (ERA5-based, 1979–present) |\n",
    "| **GloFAS Forecast** | Medium-range ensemble forecasts (up to 30 days ahead) |\n",
    "| **GloFAS Seasonal** | Long-range ensemble forecasts (up to 4 months ahead) |\n",
    "\n",
    "GloFAS models discharge in rivers worldwide at a ~0.05° spatial resolution using the LISFLOOD hydrological model driven by ECMWF atmospheric data.\n",
    "\n",
    "### What is the EWDS?\n",
    "\n",
    "The **CEMS Early Warning Data Store (EWDS)** is the central portal to access all GloFAS and EFAS data products. It provides:\n",
    "\n",
    "- A **web interface** for interactive data exploration and download\n",
    "- A **Python API** for programmatic, automated access\n",
    "- Free and open access to all products\n",
    "\n",
    "🌐 Access it at: **https://ewds.climate.copernicus.eu**"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
