    "---\n",
    "## Step 1 – Set Up Your API Credentials\n",
    "\n",
    "To access data from the EWDS programmatically you need a **Personal Access Token**.\n",
    "\n",
    "**How to get your token:**\n",
    "1. Go to [https://ewds.climate.copernicus.eu](https://ewds.climate.copernicus.eu) and register or log in\n",
    "2. Click your name in the top-right corner and open your **Profile** page\n",
    "3. Copy your **API Token** (a long alphanumeric string)\n",
    "\n",
    "The code below saves your credentials to the `~/.cdsapirc` configuration file, which is read automatically by both `cdsapi` and `earthkit-data`."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
     "import getpass\n",
     "\n",
     "# ──────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
     "# Provide your API token\n",
     "# - Option 1: set an environment variable EWDS_API_TOKEN\n",
     "# - Option 2: paste it when prompted (input hidden)\n",
     "# ──────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
     "API_TOKEN = os.environ.get(\"EWDS_API_TOKEN\")\n",
     "if not API_TOKEN:\n",
     "    API_TOKEN = getpass.getpass(\"Enter your EWDS API token (input hidden): \").strip()\n",
     "if not API_TOKEN or API_TOKEN.startswith(\"<\"):\n",
     "    raise ValueError(\"Please provide a valid EWDS API token (do not leave the placeholder).\")\n",
     "\n",
     "# EWDS API endpoint\n",
     "API_URL = \"https://ewds.climate.copernicus.eu/api\"\n",
     "\n",
     "# Write credentials to ~/.cdsapirc (do not overwrite an existing file)\n",
     "config_path = os.path.expanduser(\"~/.cdsapirc\")\n",
     "if os.path.exists(config_path):\n",
     "    print(f\"{config_path} already exists — leaving it unchanged.\")\n",
     "else:\n",
     "    with open(config_path, \"w\") as f:\n",
     "        f.write(f\"url: {API_URL}\\nkey: {API_TOKEN}\\n\")\n",
     "    print(f\"Credentials saved to {config_path}\")\n",
     "\n",
     "print(\"You only need to do this once per environment.\")"}
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    ":::{note}\n",
    "Once your `~/.cdsapirc` file is in place you do not need to run the cell above again. Both `cdsapi` and `earthkit-data` will pick up your credentials automatically.\n",
