    "---\n",
    "## Step 2 – What Data Are We Working With?\n",
    "\n",
    "In this notebook we will download **GloFAS Reanalysis version 4** data.\n",
    "\n",
    "This is a reconstruction of past river discharge values from 1979 to the present, produced by driving the LISFLOOD hydrological model with the ERA5 atmospheric reanalysis. It is the reference dataset for:\n",
    "\n",
    "- Calculating flood return periods and return levels\n",
    "- Defining hydrological thresholds (e.g., 2-year return period)\n",
    "- Validating forecasts against a consistent historical baseline\n",
    "- Understanding long-term hydrological trends\n",
    "\n",
    "**Dataset on EWDS:** [cems-glofas-reanalysis](https://ewds.climate.copernicus.eu/datasets/cems-glofas-reanalysis)\n",
    "\n",
    "### Our Case Study: The Ganges River Basin\n",
    "\n",
    "We will focus on a region covering part of **South Asia** (the Ganges–Brahmaputra basin), one of the most flood-prone regions in the world. This gives us large, clearly visible discharge signals and is relevant to many countries attending this training.\n",
    "\n",
     "| Parameter | Value |\n",
     "|---|---|\n",
     "| Variable | River discharge in the last 24 hours (`dis24`) |\n",
     "| Area | 35°N, 65°E to 10°N, 98°E |\n",
     "| Period | 2000–2005 (6 years; one date per month for download speed) |"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Step 3 – Download Data with earthkit-data\n",
    "\n",
    "We use `earthkit.data.from_source()` to request data directly from the EWDS. This is the preferred approach because:\n",
    "\n",
    "- It returns an **earthkit FieldList** object that can be immediately explored\n",
    "- It caches data locally so repeat calls are fast\n",
    "- It uses the same API syntax as `cdsapi`, so it is easy to switch between them\n",
    "\n",
    "The `\"cds\"` source tells earthkit to connect to a Copernicus Data Store (both CDS and EWDS are supported)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "tags": [
     "request"
    ]
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "# Define the dataset and request parameters\n",
    "# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "dataset = \"cems-glofas-reanalysis\"\n",
    "\n",
    "request = {\n",
    "    # Use version 4 of the GloFAS reanalysis\n",
    "    \"system_version\": \"version_4_0\",\n",
    "\n",
    "    # LISFLOOD is the hydrological model used by GloFAS\n",
    "    \"hydrological_model\": \"lisflood\",\n",
    "\n",
    "    # We want consolidated (final quality-controlled) data\n",
    "    \"product_type\": \"consolidated\",\n",
    "\n",
    "    # River discharge averaged over the last 24 hours\n",
    "    \"variable\": \"river_discharge_in_the_last_24_hours\",\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Time period: 2000 to 2005\n",
    "    \"year\": [str(y) for y in range(2000, 2006)],\n",
    "\n",
    "    # All 12 months\n",
    "    \"month\": [f\"{m:02d}\" for m in range(1, 13)],\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Use the 1st of each month to keep the download small\n",
    "    \"day\": [\"01\"],\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Output in NetCDF format (easier to work with than GRIB for beginners)\n",
    "    \"data_format\": \"netcdf4\",\n",
    "    \"download_format\": \"unarchived\",\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Bounding box: [North, West, South, East]\n",
    "    # Covering South Asia (Ganges–Brahmaputra basin)\n",
    "    \"area\": [35, 65, 10, 98],\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "# Download the data using earthkit-data\n",
    "# This may take a few minutes the first time\n",
    "# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "print(\"Requesting data from EWDS...\")\n",
    "data = ekd.from_source(\"cds\", dataset, request)\n",
    "print(\"Download complete!\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
