    "---\n",
    "## Step 5 – Convert to xarray\n",
    "\n",
    "While earthkit is excellent for data access and inspection, `xarray` is the standard tool for labelled multi-dimensional data analysis in Python. earthkit makes conversion seamless."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Convert the entire earthkit dataset to an xarray Dataset in one line\n",
    "ds = data.to_xarray()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Display the dataset structure\n",
    "# This shows dimensions, coordinates, and variables with their shapes and attributes\n",
    "print(ds)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Inspect the discharge variable specifically\n",
    "# The variable is called 'dis24' in GloFAS data (discharge in last 24 h)\n",
    "dis = ds[\"dis24\"]\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"=== Discharge Variable ===\")\n",
    "print(f\"Dimensions  : {dis.dims}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Shape       : {dis.shape}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Units       : {dis.attrs.get('units', 'not specified')}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Time range  : {str(dis.time.values[0])[:10]} → {str(dis.time.values[-1])[:10]}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Latitude    : {float(dis.latitude.min()):.2f}° to {float(dis.latitude.max()):.2f}°N\")\n",
    "print(f\"Longitude   : {float(dis.longitude.min()):.2f}° to {float(dis.longitude.max()):.2f}°E\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Step 6 – Extract a Time Series for a Specific Location\n",
    "\n",
    "In flood early warning, we often need to monitor discharge at specific **gauge stations** or **reporting points**. Here we extract a time series at a point near **Hardinge Bridge**, a key monitoring station on the lower Ganges in Bangladesh.\n",
    "\n",
    "| Station | Approximate Coordinates |\n",
    "|---|---|\n",
    "| Hardinge Bridge (Ganges, Bangladesh) | 24.08°N, 89.02°E |"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "# Define the location of interest\n",
    "# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "STATION_NAME = \"Hardinge Bridge (Ganges, Bangladesh)\"\n",
    "STATION_LAT  = 24.08   # degrees North\n",
    "STATION_LON  = 89.02   # degrees East\n",
    "\n",
    "# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "# Select the nearest grid point using xarray's sel() with method='nearest'\n",
    "# This finds the grid cell closest to our coordinates\n",
    "# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "ts = ds[\"dis24\"].sel(\n",
    "    latitude=STATION_LAT,\n",
    "    longitude=STATION_LON,\n",
    "    method=\"nearest\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Convert to a pandas Series for easy time series manipulation\n",
    "ts_series = ts.to_series()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Station     : {STATION_NAME}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Grid point  : {float(ts.latitude):.2f}°N, {float(ts.longitude):.2f}°E\")\n",
    "print(f\"Time steps  : {len(ts_series)}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Period      : {ts_series.index[0].date()} to {ts_series.index[-1].date()}\")\n",
    "print()\n",
    "print(\"First five values:\")\n",
    "print(ts_series.head())"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Step 7 – Plot the Discharge Hydrograph\n",
    "\n",
    "A **hydrograph** is a time series plot of river discharge. It is the most fundamental tool in flood hydrology and shows:\n",
    "\n",
    "- Seasonal variations (e.g., monsoon peaks)\n",
    "- Long-term trends\n",
    "- Individual flood events\n",
    "\n",
    "Let us plot the full 5-year time series."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "# Plot the hydrograph\n",
    "# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 5))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Draw the discharge time series as a filled area + line\n",
    "ax.fill_between(ts_series.index, ts_series.values, alpha=0.2, color=\"steelblue\")\n",
    "ax.plot(ts_series.index, ts_series.values, color=\"steelblue\", linewidth=1.5,\n",
    "        label=\"River discharge\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Highlight the peak discharge\n",
    "peak_date  = ts_series.idxmax()\n",
    "peak_value = ts_series.max()\n",
    "ax.axvline(peak_date, color=\"red\", linestyle=\"--\", linewidth=1.2, label=f\"Peak: {peak_value:,.0f} m³/s\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Formatting\n",
    "ax.set_title(f\"GloFAS Reanalysis – Discharge Hydrograph\\n{STATION_NAME}\",\n",
    "             fontsize=13, fontweight=\"bold\")\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel(\"Date\")\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel(\"River Discharge [m³/s]\")\n",
    "ax.xaxis.set_major_formatter(mdates.DateFormatter(\"%Y-%m\"))\n",
    "ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(mdates.MonthLocator(interval=6))\n",
    "plt.xticks(rotation=30, ha=\"right\")\n",
    "ax.grid(True, alpha=0.3)\n",
    "ax.legend()\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"\\nPeak discharge of {peak_value:,.0f} m³/s occurred on {peak_date.date()}\")\n",
    "print(\"Notice the strong annual cycle – the peak occurs during the monsoon season (July–September).\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Step 8 – Monthly Climatology\n",
    "\n",
    "A **climatology** summarises the typical seasonal pattern by averaging over all years. We group our time series by month and calculate the mean discharge for each month.\n",
    "\n",
    "This is the foundation for calculating **flood thresholds** (e.g., the 2-year return period), which we will cover in a later notebook."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "# Calculate monthly climatology\n",
    "# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "\n",
    "# Group by month (1 = January, 12 = December) and compute statistics\n",
    "monthly_mean = ts_series.groupby(ts_series.index.month).mean()\n",
    "monthly_max  = ts_series.groupby(ts_series.index.month).max()\n",
    "monthly_min  = ts_series.groupby(ts_series.index.month).min()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Month labels for the x-axis\n",
    "month_labels = [\"Jan\", \"Feb\", \"Mar\", \"Apr\", \"May\", \"Jun\",\n",
    "                \"Jul\", \"Aug\", \"Sep\", \"Oct\", \"Nov\", \"Dec\"]\n",
    "\n",
    "# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "# Plot the climatology\n",
    "# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 5))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Shaded range (min to max) shows inter-annual variability\n",
    "ax.fill_between(\n",
    "    monthly_mean.index,\n",
    "    monthly_min.values,\n",
    "    monthly_max.values,\n",
    "    alpha=0.25, color=\"steelblue\", label=\"Min–Max range\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Mean line\n",
    "ax.plot(monthly_mean.index, monthly_mean.values,\n",
    "        color=\"steelblue\", linewidth=2.5, marker=\"o\", label=\"Monthly mean\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Formatting\n",
    "ax.set_xticks(range(1, 13))\n",
    "ax.set_xticklabels(month_labels)\n",
    "ax.set_title(\n",
    "    f\"Monthly Discharge Climatology (2000–2005)\\n{STATION_NAME}\",\n",
    "    fontsize=13, fontweight=\"bold\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel(\"Month\")\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel(\"River Discharge [m³/s]\")\n",
    "ax.grid(True, alpha=0.3)\n",
    "ax.legend()\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Print a summary table\n",
    "print(\"\\nMonthly mean discharge summary:\")\n",
    "summary = pd.DataFrame({\n",
    "    \"Month\": month_labels,\n",
    "    \"Mean [m³/s]\": monthly_mean.values.round(0),\n",
    "    \"Min [m³/s]\": monthly_min.values.round(0),\n",
    "    \"Max [m³/s]\": monthly_max.values.round(0),\n",
    "})\n",
    "summary[\"Month\"] = summary[\"Month\"].astype(str)\n",
    "print(summary.to_string(index=False))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**Interpretation:**\n",
    "\n",
    "The plot shows that:\n",
    "- Discharge is **very low from December to May** (dry season)\n",
    "- Discharge rises sharply from **June** as the South Asian monsoon brings heavy rainfall\n",
    "- The **peak occurs in August or September**\n",
    "- Discharge falls rapidly in **October and November**\n",
    "\n",
    "This strong seasonal signal is characteristic of monsoon-influenced rivers and is critical context for flood early warning operations."
   ]
  },
